<div class="modal" id="search-help-modal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="exampleModalLongTitle">
  <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h5 class="modal-title" id="exampleModalLongTitle">Instructions:</h5>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
          <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
      	<h2>Welcome to the PrecisionLink UI! (powered by PIC-SURE)</h2>
      	<p>This app is intended to work as closely as possible to your favorite search engine. You can enter any search term and we will present you with a series of results that can be used to filter subsets of the data. There are many phenotypes in the system, try entering "asthma" and press enter. You will find several tabs of search results.</p>

              <p>Some search results are marked as (Category) results.  These results show that an entire hierarchy of data is available under the result that matched the search term.  Selecting a (Category) result will return all of the patients who have any value stored somewhere in that hierarchy.   </p>

<p> Below are the categories of data available:  </p>

<ul class="data-categories-list">

<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Allergies</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Bio Specimens</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Clinic Site</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Demographics</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Diagnosis</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Genotype Array</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Insurance Payors</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Laboratory Results</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Medications</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Next Generation Sequencing</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Notes</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Procedures</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Protocols</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Service</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>Vital Signs</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>WES</li></div>
<div class="col-md-4 left"><li>WGS</li></div>

</ul>

<div class="col-md-12 small-spacer"></div>
<br/>
<div class="col-md-12">
<p>When you select a search result, you will be presented with options to filter your subset using this phenotype or variant annotation. Phenotype filters apply directly to patients. If you filter by age less than 50, you will only have patients included in your patient counts and export data that match that filter. Variant annotations apply to patients' genomic data. In order for patients to be included, they must match ALL of the phenotype filters that you have added to your query as well as have at least one variant that matches ALL of your variant annotation filters. </p>
</div>

<div class="col-md-12">
	  <p>
	  </div>
	  <div class="col-md-12">
	  You can search for the Batch Name to find a particular batch of genomic data.
	  </div>
	  <div class="col-md-12 small-spacer"></div>
	  <div class="col-md-12">

     <table class="batch-table">
     <tr class="batch-table-header">
     	<th>Batch Name</th>
     	<th>Data Type</th>
     	<th>Diagnosis</th>
     	<th>Data Collection</th>
     </tr>

     {{#each genomicBatches}}
	     <tr class="batch-table-row">
	     	<td>{{name}}</td>
	     	<td>{{dataType}}</td>
	     	<td>{{diagnosis}}</td>
	     	<td>{{collectionDate}}</td>
	     </tr>
     {{/each}}

     </table>
     </div>
      </div> <!-- end modal body -->
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary close">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
